params.aAmount: positive to indicate token0, negative to indicate token1
params.aData: calls to with this data, in the event of a flash swap
params.aExactIn: true to indicate an exact in trade, false to indicate an exact out trade
params.aTo: address to send the output token and leftover input tokens, callee for the flash swap

MAX_PLATFORM_FEE().notice: Maximum allowed platform fee, which is 100%.

MAX_SWAP_FEE().notice: Maximum allowed swap fee, which is 2%.

customPlatformFee().notice: Custom platformFee override for the pair, max uint256 indicates no override.

customSwapFee().notice: Custom swap fee override for the pair, max uint256 indicates no override.

swap(int256,bool,address,bytes).notice: Swaps one token for another. The router must prefund this contract and ensure there isn't too much         slippage.
